Cannot understand inference based on generic type parameters

I'm trying to create a method create for a class that is able to "forward" some of the parameters that I'm passing it to the method build of another object, which will be instantiated in this method's implementation. The base class of these objects looks like this (for reference): export default abstract class CustomEmbed { public abstract build(...args: T): Promise; (1 more line was trimmed) And these are two subclasses of CustomEmbed which seem to be running into some sort of conflict: GeneralErrorEmbedPreset.ts export default class GeneralErrorEmbedPreset extends CustomEmbed { public override async build() { (4 more lines were trimmed) CustomErrorEmbedPreset.ts export default class CustomErrorEmbedPreset extends CustomEmbed<[string]> { public override async build(reason: string) { (4 more lines were trimmed) And the class whose create method is giving me a (very) hard time: export enum PresetEmbedType { CustomError = 'CustomError', (26 more lines were trimmed) There are a couple of things I don't understand:
If I hover over the second assignment expression for embed , TS complains: Type 'CustomErrorEmbedPreset' is not assignable to type 'PresetEmbeds[U]'. Type 'CustomErrorEmbedPreset' is not assignable to type 'CustomErrorEmbedPreset & GeneralErrorEmbedPreset & CustomEmbed'. (4 more lines were trimmed) In my interpretation, TS should infer, through the switch clause, that if, for example, type (to which is assigned the U generic type parameter) is PresetEmbedType.GeneralError , then embed ( PresetEmbeds[U] ) should be inferred as PresetEmbeds[PresetEmbedType.GeneralError] - and the same thing should apply for every other branch of the switch. Clearly this is not what's happening so my interpretation is wrong! TS also complains about the spread argument in embed.build : A spread argument must either have a tuple type or be passed to a rest parameter.ts(2556) which I also don't understand, since the type of PresetEmbeds[U]['build'] will always be a rest parameter, since all of them are subclasses of CustomEmbed , whose build type signature confirms it. I'm using Typescript version 5.7.3
"ERR_MODULE_NOT_FOUND" error when using TypeScript project references

I'm trying to implement TypeScript's project references to be able import code from a common package between my application's services. This is how the tsconfig.json of the shared package ( database_models ) is setup: { "extends": "@tsconfig/node-lts/tsconfig.json", (10 more lines were trimmed) And the main package's tsconfig.json : { "extends": "@tsconfig/node-lts/tsconfig.json", (17 more lines were trimmed) The import: import UsersModel from "@database_models/UsersModel.js"; Throws this error: node:internal/modules/esm/resolve:854 throw new ERR_MODULE_NOT_FOUND(packageName, fileURLToPath(base), null); (15 more lines were trimmed) I'm building the main package's files using tsc --build . Here's what I've double-checked:
The paths value in the main package's tsconfig.json is pointing to the correct path. Made sure to re-build the common package's files after setting composite: true in its tsconfig.json
